This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it deals with optimisations for a runtime-verification tool for Erlang programs. It could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it involves improving the performance of a tool used for verifying software correctness. Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) are also possible sub-categories as the tool deals with concurrent monitors and optimisations for their synthesis. Finally, Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) is a possible sub-category as the tool involves verifying correctness properties.
